@node Requirements
@section Requirements

@itemize
@item
Emacs with Org mode available.
@item
A writable directory next to each commented Org source file for local
sidecar files.
@item
Optional backend packages for remote providers, such as @samp{org-confluence}.
@end itemize

@node Installation from a checkout
@section Installation from a checkout

Add the package directory to @samp{load-path} and require the package:

@lisp
(add-to-list 'load-path "/path/to/org-comments")
(require 'org-comments)
@end lisp

Then enable @samp{org-comments-mode} in Org buffers.  This minor mode is the main
user entry point for commands, keybindings, and overlays:

@lisp
(add-hook 'org-mode-hook #'org-comments-mode)
@end lisp

For a commands-only setup without inline/page markers, set
@samp{org-comments-enable-overlays} before enabling the mode:

@lisp
(setq org-comments-enable-overlays nil)
(add-hook 'org-mode-hook #'org-comments-mode)
@end lisp

@node Minimal workflow
@section Minimal workflow

@enumerate
@item
Open an Org file.
@item
Enable @samp{org-comments-mode}.
@item
Select a region and run @samp{M-x org-comments-create}.
@item
Open the side panel with @samp{M-x org-comments-open}.
@item
Navigate comments with @samp{org-comments-next} and @samp{org-comments-previous}.
@end enumerate

See *note Commands:: and *note Keybindings:: for the generated reference.

