@node Developer API
@chapter Developer API

Use public @samp{org-comments-*} functions for package integration.  Functions with
an @samp{org-comments--} prefix are private implementation details and should not be
called by backend packages.

Important extension areas:

@itemize
@item
backend registration in @samp{org-comments-backend.el};
@item
UI adapter variables in @samp{org-comments-ui.el} and panel action modules;
@item
collaboration normalization in @samp{org-comments-collaboration.el};
@item
explicit migration helpers in @samp{org-comments-migrate.el}.
@end itemize

@node Troubleshooting
@chapter Troubleshooting

@menu
* No comments appear::
* Legacy sidecar error::
* Remote operation is unsupported::
* Info manual is missing::
@end menu

@node No comments appear
@section No comments appear

Check that the source buffer is visiting a file and that the sibling
@samp{.comments.org} file exists.  Local sidecars are file-backed.

@node Legacy sidecar error
@section Legacy sidecar error

If collection reports legacy metadata, run @samp{M-x org-comments-migrate-sidecar}
on the sidecar file and retry.

@node Remote operation is unsupported
@section Remote operation is unsupported

Backends advertise capabilities.  If a backend does not support push, pull,
sync, or remote open, the generic command reports a clear unsupported operation
error.

@node Info manual is missing
@section Info manual is missing

Build the manual from the repository checkout:

@example
devenv -q shell -- docs:org-comments
@end example

Then add the package @samp{docs/} directory to @samp{Info-directory-list} or install the
Info file into your site Info directory.

@bye
